      ["LORE"] = "To the east of the Hill of Erech and abutting the pass known as Tarlang's Neck lies Lancrath, a hamlet inhabited by farmers, crafters, and traders. Before Lord Duinhir's return from the War and the retaking of Tingobel, many of the mining village's displaced refugees sought for shelter and found welcome among the kind folk of Lancrath."; 
